casebody.data:
Browne, Respondent, v. Forty-Second St., M. & St. N. A. R. Co., Appellant. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. December 19,1889.)

Argued before Van Hoesen, P. J., and Bookstavee, J.

W. C. Trull, for appellant. J. H. McCarthy, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be reversed, unless plaintiff consents to reduce to $25 damages, and the costs recoverable in the district court on a judgment for that amount.
